FBIS4-5819 "dreas072_c_94007" FBIS-EAS-94-072 Daily Report 12 Apr 1994 North Korea U.S. Deployment of Military Airplanes Denounced U.S. Deployment of Military Airplanes Denounced SK1304141894 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in Korean 1300 GMT 12 Apr 94 SK1304141894 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in Korean 1300 GMT 12 Apr 94 Korean BFN [Text] According to a military source, the U.S. imperialists on 10 and 11 April mobilized and deployed 20-odd military planes of various types in South Korea from overseas bases, thus committing a crime. Formations of assault planes and pursuit-assault planes that took off from bases in Japan on 11 April flew into U.S. Air Force bases in South Korea. Prior to this, on 10 April, various types of military aircraft, including F-15, F-4, FA-18, AV-8 and EA-6, were mobilized and deployed to South Korea from U.S. bases in Japan and the Pacific area. In addition, on 10 and 11 April, C-5 ultra-large strategic transport airplanes carrying a large number of troops and lethal equipment from bases on the U.S. mainland and the Pacific region and C-130 and C-141 transport airplanes landed in U.S. Air Force bases in South Korea and airlifted troops were mobilized and deployed to the operational zones and war equipment was supplied to these zones. Our people and the People's Army are watching with vigilance the war preparation moves of the U.S. imperialists and the South Korean puppets. If the rascals perpetrate an act of aggression, we will deal a resolute punishment to them.
